headline: Fully electric vehicle sales in EU overtake petrol for first time
summary:
STORY: Fully electric car sales in December overtook petrol for the first time in the European Union.

That was despite policymakers proposing to loosen emissions regulations.

Tesla continued to lose market share though, particularly to competitors including China's BYD and Europe's best-selling group Volkswagen.

That was according to data from the European auto lobby ACEA.

Car sales throughout Europe sustained a sixth straight month of year-on-year growth.

Overall registrations, a proxy for sales, hit their highest volumes in five years in 2025.

Europe's car industry faces challenges including competition from China, U.S. import tariffs and difficulties in meeting domestic regulations for EV adoption.

The EU unveiled in December a plan to abandon an effective 2035 ban on combustion engine cars, bowing to calls from struggling carmakers.

But analysts expect EVs to gain in  popularity despite the policy relaxation.

Sales in the EU, Britain and the European Free Trade Association rose by 7.6% to 1.2 million cars in December.

They were up over 10% at VW and 4.5% at Stelantis.

They fell 2.2% at Renault though. 

And registrations at Tesla were down over a fifth.

Competitor BYD saw a 229% rise.

headline: Tesla’s Price Target Is Rising Even as Its Profit Outlook Tanks
summary: “Tesla is truly unique in capital markets,” said Nicholas Colas, co-founder at DataTrek Research.  Over the past 12 months, the average forecast for Tesla’s 2026 net income has tumbled 56% from $14.1 billion to $6.1 billion.  The stock is up 7% in that time after closing Tuesday at $435.20, well above Wall Street’s expectations for a year from now.

headline: Obi Releases Data Analysis of Tesla and Waymo Rideshare Pricing, Wait Times, and Sentiments

headline: Tesla’s Price Targets Rise Even as Its Profit Outlook Tanks
summary: Wall Street is giving off mixed signals about Tesla Inc. Analysts are increasingly skeptical of the electric-vehicle maker’s earnings potential this year, but their expectations for the company’s stock price keep climbing.  “Tesla is truly unique in capital markets,” said Nicholas Colas, co-founder at DataTrek Research.  Over the past 12 months, the average forecast for Tesla’s 2026 net income has tumbled 56% from $14.1 billion to $6.1 billion as of Monday’s close.

headline: Pilot Partners with Tesla on Semi Charger Network for Fleets
summary: KNOXVILLE, Tenn., January 27, 2026--Pilot Travel Centers LLC ("Pilot"), the nation’s largest operator of travel centers, has entered into an agreement with Tesla to install Semi Chargers to facilitate heavy-duty electric vehicle truck charging. The Tesla charging stations will be built at select Pilot locations along I-5, I-10, and several major corridors where the need for heavy-duty charging is highest. The first sites are expected to open in Summer 2026.

headline: The Weather is Freezing but Stocks Are Hot. It’s the January Effect.
summary: With the U.S. digging out from Winter Storm Fern, and counting the cost of an arctic blast that could bring record cold readings as far south as the Florida Keys, investors are also taking the temperature of perhaps the most important stretch of the year for the stock market.  Labeled the “January Barometer” by famed academic Yale Hirsch, creator of the Stock Trader’s Almanac, the idea of extrapolating first- month returns over the calendar year has proven to be a winner.  Adam Turnquist, chief technical strategist at  LPL Financial  notes data showing that since 1950, the  has generated an average return of nearly 17% in years when the benchmark ends January in positive territory.

content.title: The Weather is Freezing but Stocks Are Hot. It’s the January Effect.
